.TH UTILITYKIT 1 "July 2026" "UtilityKit v5.10.6" "UtilityKit Tools"
.SH NAME
utility-duplicate_finder \- Detect exact duplicate files in a directory tree using a two-stage approach — size comparison first, then content hashing — and optionally delete duplicates or replace them with hardlinks.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B utility duplicate_finder
[\fIoptions\fP]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Detect exact duplicate files in a directory tree using a two-stage approach — size comparison first, then content hashing — and optionally delete duplicates or replace them with hardlinks.
.SH FEATURES
.PP
.IP \(bu 4
\fBTwo-stage detection\fP — matches file sizes first to avoid hashing every file, then confirms duplicates by hash
.IP \(bu 4
\fBMultiple actions\fP — report only, delete duplicates, or replace duplicates with hardlinks
.IP \(bu 4
\fBSafe by default\fP — dry-run preview is shown before any files are modified
.IP \(bu 4
\fBVersion control aware\fP — automatically skips \fC.git\fP, \fC.hg\fP, and \fC.svn\fP directories
.IP \(bu 4
\fBInteractive mode\fP — running without arguments launches a guided prompt
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH USAGE
.PP
.EX
bash _duplicate_finder/_duplicate_finder.sh

bash _duplicate_finder/_duplicate_finder.sh ~/Downloads

bash _duplicate_finder/_duplicate_finder.sh ~/Downloads --delete

bash _duplicate_finder/_duplicate_finder.sh ~/Downloads --delete --apply

bash _duplicate_finder/_duplicate_finder.sh ~/Downloads --hardlink --apply

bash _duplicate_finder/_duplicate_finder.sh ~/Pictures --delete --apply
.EE
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
Option   |   Description
\fCDIR\fP   |   Directory to scan (default: \fC.\fP)
\fC--delete\fP   |   Delete duplicate copies, keeping the first file per hash
\fC--hardlink\fP   |   Replace duplicates with hardlinks pointing to the first file
\fC--apply\fP   |   Execute the chosen action (dry-run preview if omitted)
\fC-h, --help\fP   |   Show usage
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH HOW DUPLICATES ARE DETECTED
.PP
.IP \(em 4
Every file under the target directory is scanned and grouped by byte size
.IP \(em 4
Files in groups with more than one member are hashed using \fCsha256sum\fP (falls back to \fCshasum -a 256\fP, then \fCmd5sum\fP)
.IP \(em 4
Files sharing the same hash are confirmed duplicates
.IP \(em 4
The first file encountered for each hash is kept — all others are the duplicates
.PP
This approach avoids hashing large files unnecessarily, making scans fast even on directories with thousands of files.
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH ACTION REFERENCE
.PP
Action   |   Effect on duplicates   |   Originals
report   |   No changes   |   Untouched
delete   |   Duplicate files are permanently removed   |   Kept
hardlink   |   Duplicate paths are replaced with hardlinks to the original   |   Kept, now shared inode
.PP
Hardlinking saves disk space while keeping both file paths accessible. Both paths point to the same data on disk. Editing one will affect the other.
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH OUTPUT PREVIEW
.PP
.EX
  Duplicate groups found
  ------------------------------------------------

  Keep:   ~/Downloads/photo.jpg
  Dupe:   ~/Downloads/photo_copy.jpg  (will be removed if applied)

  Keep:   ~/Downloads/report.pdf
  Dupe:   ~/Downloads/report (1).pdf  (will be removed if applied)
.EE
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH EXIT CODES
.PP
Code   |   Meaning
\fC0\fP   |   Success
\fC1\fP   |   Unknown option passed
